OL,7,FMr Hughes concluded the trio died as a
OL,8,Fresult of a road traffic collision. He
OL,9,Fsaid the effect of alcohol in Jesse's
OL,10,Fblood was unlikely to have materially
OL,11,Fcontributed to the collision.
OL,13,FMr Hughes said he came to that
OL,14,Fdetermination based on Jesse's manner
OL,15,Fwhen he left the Tonyrefail working
OL,16,Fmen's club and on the basis that if
OL,17,Fthe passengers in the car had felt
OL,18,FJesse was not in a fit state to drive
OL,19,Fthey would have interfered.
